<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>Stage 2: Insecure cookies</h1>
    </div>
    <p>
      Congrats! You have completed Stage 1.
    </p>
    <p>
      This page sets an insecure cookie after
      a successful login. Let's try to mess with it so we can log in as
      someone else.
    </p>
    <p>
      There's a user <code>bob</code> with a very insecure password
      <code>baseball</code>
    </p>
    <p>
      Log in as Bob and see what the cookie looks like.
      Then try to log in as <code>admin</code>.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can read cookies in the DevTools console
      <pre><code>document.cookie</code></pre>
      You can update cookies too:
      <pre><code>document.cookie = 'COOKIE NAME=COOKIE VALUE'</code></pre>
    </p>
    <p>
      Or you can install
      <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/cookies/iphcomljdfghbkdcfndaijbokpgddeno?hl=en">Cookies Chrome extension</a>
      to view and modify your cookies.
    </p>
    <button class="btn btn-default" onclick="$('.hint').show()">Reveal hint</button>
    <p class="hint">
      Set the cookie <code>user</code> to the value <code>admin</code>.
    </p>
    {{#unless user}}
    <h3>Success, you logged in as admin! <a href="/{{stage3}}">Go to stage 3.</a></h3>

    <form method="post" action='/{{stage2}}' class="form-inline" style="margin-top: 10px">
      Username: <input type="text" name="username">
      Password: <input type="text" name="password">
      <input type="submit" value="Login">
    </form>
    {{else}}
      <h2>Logged in as: {{user}}</h2>
      {{#if admin}}
        <h3>Success, you logged in as admin! <a href="/{{stage3}}">Go to stage 3.</a></h3>
      {{/if}}
    {{/unless}}
  </div>
</div>

